    "id": 4980,
    "slug": "googles-vision-for-2026-building-a-revenue-engine-powered-by-data",
    "title": "Google’s Vision for 2026: Building a Revenue Engine Powered by Data",
    "seoTitle": "Google’s Vision for 2026: Building a Revenue Engine Powered by Data | Found Search Marketing",
    "excerpt": "Last week, I had the privilege of attending Google’s Rethink ROI with Julie Warnecke in New York City, an event focused on AI-powered, first-party data-driven approaches to more accurate measurement and stronger return on investment...",
    "publishedAt": "2026-02-18",
    "publishedLabel": "February 18, 2026",
    "authorName": "Adam Persinger",
    "authorTitle": "Head of Strategic Media",
    "authorUrl": "",
    "heroImage": "https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/nycfromoffice.webp",
    "heroImageAlt": "",
    "contentHtml": "<section class=\"blog-post__intro article-content\"><h2>Clean First-Party Data is Your AI Foundation</h2>\n<p>Last week, I had the privilege of attending Google’s Rethink ROI with Julie Warnecke in New York City, an event focused on AI-powered, first-party data-driven approaches to more accurate measurement and stronger return on investment strategies.</p>\n<p>The event featured a strong speaker lineup from Google and industry leaders, along with previews of upcoming releases, but one message stood out in nearly every session:<strong> If you want to win in this next era, your first-party data must be clean, consolidated, and activation-ready. That was not a side note. It was the foundation.</strong></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><figure class=\"blog-post__figure\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"432\" src=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/dataengine-768x432.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/dataengine-768x432.webp 768w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/dataengine-300x169.webp 300w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/dataengine-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/dataengine.webp 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</figure><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><p>Every brand will have access to similar AI tools. Every competitor will be operating in the same platforms. The differentiator will not be access to technology. It will be the quality, structure, and usability of your own data.</p>\n<p>Whether it is advanced attribution, more accessible marketing mix modeling, or simplified KPIs that truly reflect business impact and can be shared across teams, it all stems from your data infrastructure. When your data is unified and reliable, you can measure more accurately, optimize with greater confidence, and communicate marketing’s value more clearly across your organization.</p>\n<p>Google is building the ecosystem. The brands that will benefit most are the ones that treat their data as a strategic asset rather than just a reporting tool.</p>\n<p>2026 will not reward marketers who simply adopt new tools. It will reward those who build the foundation that allows those tools to perform.</p>\n<p>That foundation is what will unlock the next generation of marketing tactics, measurement capabilities, and revenue engineering processes that Google is bringing to market in 2026 and beyond.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><section class=\"blog-post__cta article-content\"><p><strong>Want to know where your setup stands and how to scale smarter with compliant first-party data? </strong><a href=\"https://foundsm.com/DataConnect/?utm_source=owned&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=ICDPA%20Blog%20Post&amp;utm_term=Foundblog&amp;utm_content=CTA\"><strong>Contact us</strong></a><strong> today for a data consultation.&nbsp;</strong></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section>",
