    "slug": "a-3-minute-implementation-guide-to-segmenting-ai-traffic-in-ga4",
    "title": "A 3 Minute Implementation Guide to Segmenting AI Traffic in GA4",
    "seoTitle": "A 3 Minute Implementation Guide to Segmenting AI Traffic in GA4 | Found Search Marketing",
    "excerpt": "Segmenting AI search traffic in GA4 allows you to see traffic trends from answer engines over time and analyze correlations between other traffic sources (for example, organic search). This change in Google Analytics is very...",
    "publishedAt": "2026-01-02",
    "publishedLabel": "January 2, 2026",
    "authorName": "Ryan Eme",
    "authorTitle": "Director of Data Intelligence",
    "authorUrl": "https://foundsm.com/insights/authors/ryan",
    "heroImage": "https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/GA4-Blog-image.png",
    "heroImageAlt": "",
    "contentHtml": "<section class=\"blog-post__intro article-content\"><p>Segmenting AI search traffic in GA4 allows you to see traffic trends from answer engines over time and analyze correlations between other traffic sources (for example, organic search). This change in Google Analytics is very straightforward and should not take more than 3 minutes to implement. </p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><p class=\"blog-post__button-row\"><a class=\"blog-post__button\" href=\"#video\">Watch Video</a></p><p class=\"blog-post__button-row\"><a class=\"blog-post__button\" href=\"#desktop-container\">Read Guide</a></p><figure class=\"blog-post__video\" id=\"video\"><a class=\"blog-post__video-link\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xu4-TeF7NL0\"><img src=\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Xu4-TeF7NL0/hqdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"><span class=\"blog-post__video-play\" aria-hidden=\"true\">Play</span><span class=\"u-visually-hidden\">Watch video on YouTube</span></a></figure><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><h2>Benefits of Tracking AI Traffic</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li>Gain visibility into how much traffic is being driven from AI or answer engines</li>\n<li>Compare trends over time against other channel groups</li>\n<li>Compare conversion rates and users’ propensity to convert based on AI Search vs standard organic search&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Identify areas of opportunity for additional paid media support</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><h2>How To Segment AI Traffic in GA4</h2>\t\t\t\t</section><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><h3>1. CREATE A NEW CHANNEL GROUP</h3>\n<ol>\n \t<li>In Google Analytics, navigate to the Admin panel (gear icon in lower left corner). Under Data Display, click Channel Groups.</li>\n \t<li>If you are not using custom channel groups, click the “Create new channel group” button and give it a name.</li>\n \t<li>If you already have a custom channel group for your property, click into the channel group that you want to edit.</li>\n</ol>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><figure class=\"blog-post__figure\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1649\" height=\"1104\" src=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image6.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image6.png 1649w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image6-300x201.png 300w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image6-1024x686.png 1024w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image6-768x514.png 768w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image6-1536x1028.png 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1649px) 100vw, 1649px\"></figure><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><h3>2. ADD CHANNEL</h3><ol><li>Click “Add new channel”.</li><li>Give it a name like “AI Search” or “Answer Engines”.</li></ol>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><figure class=\"blog-post__figure\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"779\" height=\"447\" src=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image1.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image1.png 779w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image1-300x172.png 300w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image1-768x441.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 779px) 100vw, 779px\"></figure><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><h3>3. ADD CONDITIONS</h3>\n<ol>\n \t<li>Add a condition where “Source” matches regex.</li>\n \t<li>Add the following regex statement:\n<code>.*(gemini|chatgpt|claude|\nperplexity|copilot).*</code><strong>\nTip: Verify this against your real AI traffic sources to ensure the regex correctly captures all relevant AI traffic.</strong></li>\n \t<li>Click “Apply” and then “Save Channel.”</li>\n</ol>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><figure class=\"blog-post__figure\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"590\" height=\"521\" src=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image2.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image2.png 590w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image2-300x265.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"></figure><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><h3>4. REORDER</h3>\n<ol>\n \t<li>Click the “Reorder” button next to “Add new channel”.</li>\n \t<li>Drag your new channel above Referral and Organic Search.</li>\n \t<li>Click “Save Group.”</li>\n</ol>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><figure class=\"blog-post__figure\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"541\" height=\"213\" src=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image7.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image7.webp 541w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image7-300x118.webp 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 541px) 100vw, 541px\"></figure><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><h3>5. WHAT’S NEXT</h3>\n<ol>\n \t<li>Navigate to Reporting → Traffic Acquisition.</li>\n \t<li>You can now segment and filter your reporting by your new custom channel group using the field dropdown.</li>\n</ol>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><figure class=\"blog-post__figure\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"789\" height=\"414\" src=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image3.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image3.webp 789w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image3-300x157.webp 300w, https://foundsm.com/found2025/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/image3-768x403.webp 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 789px) 100vw, 789px\"></figure><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><h2>Things to Consider</h2>\t\t\t\t</section><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><p>AI platforms may emerge over time which will require updates to the RegEx statement used for the custom channel group.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><section class=\"blog-post__content-section article-content\"><p>Custom Channel groups do not change how data is processed and will not impact your historical data. </p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><section class=\"blog-post__cta article-content\"><h2>Have questions about GA4?</h2>\t\t\t\t</section><section class=\"blog-post__cta article-content\"><p><a href=\"https://foundsm.com/contact-us/\">Contact Us today</a> and one of our team members will be in touch shortly. </p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section>",
